Citation.sTitle: Activity coefficients at infinite dilution measurements for organic solutes and water in the ionic liquid 4-methyl-N-butyl-pyridinium bis(trifluoromethylsulfonyl)-imide
Citation.sAbstract: The activity coefficients at infinite dilution, c1 13 for 36 solutes: alkanes, cycloalkanes, alkenes, alkynes, aromatic hydrocarbons, alcohols, thiophene, tetrahydrofuran, ethers, acetone, and water in the ionic liquid 4-methyl-N-butyl-pyridinium bis(trifluoromethylsulfonyl)-imide [bmPY][NTf2] were determined by gas liquid chromatography at temperatures from 298.15 K to 368.15 K. The partial molar excess enthalpies at infinite dilution values DHE;1 1 were calculated from the experimental c1 13 values obtained over the temperature range. The selectivity for different separation problems were calculated from the c1 13 and compared to the literature values for other ionic liquids, N-methyl-2-pyrrolidinone (NMP) and sulfolane
